+## AI Work Step JSONL Storage
+
+AI work-step records are stored in the project-scoped AI action log. The
+canonical default path is:
+
+```text
+<UnityProject>/UserSettings/LuxAiActionLog.jsonl
+```
+
+This location is intentionally under Unity `UserSettings` so it stays local to
+the project, is excluded from package source control by normal Unity workflows,
+and can be read by LUX tools, CLI/API consumers, and AI agents without a
+dedicated timeline UI.
+
+Lifecycle rules:
+
+- Path resolution is always scoped by an explicit Unity project path. Readers
+  and writers must not fall back to a process-global log when a project path is
+  available.
+- `UserSettings/LuxAiActionLog.jsonl` is the default file for editor user
+  actions, AI work steps, and runtime gameplay custom events. AI work steps use
+  `payload.kind: "ai-work-step"` inside the shared event model.
+- `ensure_log_path` creates the parent `UserSettings` directory when needed but
+  does not create an empty log file. The JSONL file is created by the first
+  append, keeping untouched projects free of empty artifacts.
+- Existing logs at the previous Phase 6 preview path,
+  `.lux/ai-action-log.jsonl`, are migrated once to the default `UserSettings`
+  path when the default file does not already exist.
+- Once active, each line is one complete UTF-8 JSON object. Readers ignore blank
+  and malformed lines; compaction keeps valid tail records, drops corrupt
+  records, writes a temporary sibling file, syncs it, and atomically replaces the
+  JSONL file.
+- Retention metadata on each event describes active/expired cleanup state.
+  Count-based compaction and later cleanup tooling must operate on the same
+  project-scoped file instead of copying events to an unscoped global timeline.
+
